- Given z = 2 + √2 − (3 + 3√2)i and c = 2 − 3i. w is z rotated around c by π/4 counterclockwise.

Work:
- Rotation around c by angle θ: w = c + e^{iθ}(z − c). Here θ = π/4, e^{iπ/4} = (1 + i)/√2.
- z − c = (2 + √2 − 2) + (−3 − 3√2 − (−3))i = √2 − 3√2 i = √2(1 − 3i).
