- Define A_i(j) = f(i, j) for i ≥ 0 and j ∈ {0,1,2,3,4}. We seek f(2015, 2) = A_{2015}(2).

Work:
- Base: A_0(j) = mod5(j+1) gives A_0 = [1, 2, 3, 4, 0].
- Compute iteratively:
  - A_1(0) = f(0,1) = 2; A_1(1) = f(0, A_1(0)) = f(0,2) = 3; A_1(2) = 4; A_1(3) = 0; A_1(4) = 1.
    So A_1 = [2, 3, 4, 0, 1].
  - A_2(0) = f(1,1) = A_1(1) = 3;
    A_2(1) = f(1, A_2(0)) = f(1,3) = A_1(3) = 0;
    A_2(2) = f(1, A_2(1)) = f(1,0) = A_1(0) = 2;
    A_2(3) = f(1, A_2(2)) = f(1,2) = A_1(2) = 4;
    A_2(4) = f(1, A_2(3)) = f(1,4) = A_1(4) = 1;
    So A_2 = [3, 0, 2, 4, 1].
  - A_3(0) = f(2,1) = A_2(1) = 0;
    A_3(1) = f(2, A_3(0)) = f(2,0) = A_2(0) = 3;
    A_3(2) = f(2, A_3(1)) = f(2,3) = A_2(3) = 4;
    A_3(3) = f(2, A_3(2)) = f(2,4) = A_2(4) = 1;
    A_3(4) = f(2, A_3(3)) = f(2,1) = A_2(1) = 0;
    So A_3 = [0, 3, 4, 1, 0].
  - A_4(0) = f(3,1) = A_3(1) = 3;
    A_4(1) = f(3, A_4(0)) = f(3,3) = A_3(3) = 1;
    A_4(2) = f(3, A_4(1)) = f(3,1) = A_3(1) = 3;
    A_4(3) = f(3, A_4(2)) = f(3,3) = A_3(3) = 1;
    A_4(4) = f(3, A_4(3)) = f(3,1) = A_3(1) = 3;
    So A_4 = [3, 1, 3, 1, 3].
  - A_5(0) = f(4,1) = A_4(1) = 1;
    A_5(1) = f(4, A_5(0)) = f(4,1) = A_4(1) = 1;
    A_5(2) = f(4, A_5(1)) = f(4,1) = 1;
    A_5(3) = f(4, A_5(2)) = f(4,1) = 1;
    A_5(4) = f(4, A_5(3)) = f(4,1) = 1;
    So A_5 = [1, 1, 1, 1, 1].

- Induction step: If for some k ≥ 5 we have A_k(j) = 1 for all j, then
  - A_{k+1}(0) = f(k, 1) = A_k(1) = 1.
